---
// Root redirect page - directs users to their preferred language or the default (English)
// This page runs when someone visits https://yoursite.com/
// It uses Astro's i18n capabilities to detect the user's browser language preference

// Redirect to the preferred language-prefixed home page
// Uses the browser's preferred locale or falls back to 'en' (English)
// 307 is a temporary redirect that preserves the HTTP method
return Astro.redirect(`/${Astro.preferredLocale || "en"}/`, 307);
---

<!--
  This empty html tag with the 'data-pagefind-ignore' attribute serves two purposes:
  1. It provides a root element to prevent the "no <html> element" warning.
  2. The attribute explicitly tells Pagefind to skip indexing this file entirely.
-->
<html data-pagefind-ignore="all"></html>
